[SPEAKER_08] Glory, glory, hallelujah.

250
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:49,000
[SPEAKER_08] His truth is marching on.

251
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:52,000
[SPEAKER_08] It was an experience I shall never forget.

252
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:58,000
[SPEAKER_07] To see the leadership of the military sing the Christian hymns for us.

253
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:01,000
[SPEAKER_07] Dressed in the uniform of what had been our greatest adversary.

254
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:04,000
[SPEAKER_07] Would just pull your heart.

255
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:09,000
[SPEAKER_03] It sent gels down my back to realize that within just a few years

256
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:13,000
[SPEAKER_03] things had changed so dramatically like that.

257
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:17,000
[SPEAKER_03] And there were soldiers in uniform that came forward at that meeting.

258
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:20,000
[SPEAKER_06] It really broke through in many ways.

259
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:25,000
[SPEAKER_06] And the events of history through Eastern Europe and all the countries he went into.

260
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:29,000
[SPEAKER_06] Breaking down the wall in Germany.

261
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:35,000
[SPEAKER_06] So many things happened as a result of Billy Graham's entry into that part of the world.

262
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:37,000
[SPEAKER_06] And preaching the gospel of peace.

263
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:48,000
[SPEAKER_04] Mr. Graham and his associates say we don't know what impact we had.

264
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:52,000
[SPEAKER_04] We do know that they took the steps that we asked them to take.

265
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,000
[SPEAKER_04] To open up seminaries.

266
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,000
[SPEAKER_04] To let Jews immigrate.

267
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:56,000
[SPEAKER_04] To open the churches.

268
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:58,000
[SPEAKER_04] The things they asked for they got.

269
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:05,000
[UNKNOWN] To open up seminaries.

270
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:24,259
[SPEAKER_01] Ovo je ovo riječ. Zato smo često nesretni, koja je dvojica učenika koje su išli iz Zemlose.

271
00:21:24,259 --> 00:21:29,779
[SPEAKER_01] Isus njih sreća nakon svoje smrti i oni njemu tužni prepričavaju šta se dogodilo.

272
00:21:30,140 --> 00:21:35,599
[SPEAKER_01] A on njima citira Božju riječ. Kaže, gdje je to pisalo da se to moramo robiti.

273
00:21:35,599 --> 00:21:41,660
[SPEAKER_01] I u njima se plako, budi nada, kaže, za ga nije boljeno srce da te govodi.

274
00:21:41,660 --> 00:21:48,779
[SPEAKER_01] Mi smo često tužni, nesretni, bezperspektivni, zato je odvjerujem u svog Isusa.

275
00:21:48,779 --> 00:21:54,480
[SPEAKER_01] Kad smo te krenuli na zajednicu, Bogu hvala na tom događaju, bilo nas još malo.

276
00:21:54,480 --> 00:22:00,299
[SPEAKER_01] Tu smo bili u kućici i došao je dan i je zub kak čovjek se izjel u tim proječkim damu i molio je za nas.

277
00:22:00,299 --> 00:22:07,259
[SPEAKER_01] I rekli mu sam jednu sliku. Gospodin je pokaza jednu sliku kako svaki od vas dolazi do svog Isusa.

278
00:22:07,259 --> 00:22:09,599
[SPEAKER_01] I nešto traži.

279
00:22:09,599 --> 00:22:14,680
[SPEAKER_01] To je Isus iz naše prekcije, kako smo si mi složili.

280
